                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16130828" author="szita" created="Thu, 17 Aug 2017 17:01:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Some unit test related targets should not depend on &lt;tt&gt;jar&lt;/tt&gt;, but rather on &lt;tt&gt;jar-simple&lt;/tt&gt; instead because:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There is no point of compiling against two versions of Spark when at the end we only use one to run the tests with&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There is no way to override what Spark version we want, it will always be spark1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Please find the fix in &lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12882394/12882394_PIG-5294.0.patch&quot; title=&quot;PIG-5294.0.patch attached to PIG-5294&quot;&gt;PIG-5294.0.patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16132149" author="nkollar" created="Fri, 18 Aug 2017 13:04:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Adam, indeed, looks like we can&apos;t execute unit test in spark2 mode right now without your patch. Looks good to me!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16132190" author="szita" created="Fri, 18 Aug 2017 13:35:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for taking a look Nandor! This is now committed to trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
